    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <date/>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>Please to send Bottle of “Hydrated Magnesia” if you have any.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> It is thicker than cream, &amp; I think slightly opake.—</p> 
                        <p>Please mark dose.—</p>
                        <p>C. Darwin <lb/> <lb/></p>
                        <p rend="left">Down. Dec. 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
               
                
                
                
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year range is conjectured from a note on the letter reading ‘About 1874?’ that may have been made by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_9414.xml">William Baxter (1861–1934)</ref>, the son of William Walmisley Baxter.</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f2">Hydrated magnesia (magnesium hydroxide; Mg(OH)<hi rend="subscript">2</hi>) was used as a purgative (<hi rend="italic">Edinburgh Medical and Surgical Journal</hi> 62 (1844): 559).</note>
            </div>
        
